Linux:

  Basic:
    System Info:
        H/W
            - CPU
                cat /proc/cpuinfo
            - MEM 
                cat /proc/meminfo
            - DISK 
                sudo fdisk -l
        S/W
            - OS Vendor
            - OS Version
                cat /etc/*release
            - OS Arch
                x86_64/x64              -> 64 bit 
                x86/i386,i586,i686      -> 32 bit

    Linux Command Syntax:
        command-name {options} {inputs}
            ex: uname
                uname -i 
                cat /proc/cpuinfo

            Options:
                -(single character) , -i -x, -s
                --(single word) , --help, --verbose

            Default option for all commands : --help

    Linux Commands help:

    List files & Dir: 
        ls 
    Files:
        Create file     - touch 
        Remove file     - rm
        Rename a file   - mv
        Copy a file     - cp

    Directories:
    Search Files & Directories:
    Utilities:
